Requirement:
Scaling and Managing Kubernetes Clusters with Amazon EKS

==================
LET'S TINKER
==================
1. Go to Amazon Elastic Kubernetes Service->Create EKS cluster
2. There two options for configuration (I have chosen custom configuration.)- 
  => Quick configuration (Cluster configuration, Networking and Observability are automatically configured; only cluster name, kubernetes version, IAM role, Subnets       need to be selected) 
  => Custom configuration (All configurations are to selected manually, nothing is default configuration. It provides more control over cluster configuration).
3. There is option to enable/disable EKS Auto mode.
    (EKS automates routine cluster tasks for compute, storage, and networking. When a new pod can't fit onto existing nodes, EKS creates a new node. EKS combines         cluster infrastructure managed by AWS with integrated Kubernetes capabilities to meet application compute needs. EKS Auto Mode includes the following                 capabilities: Application load balancing, Block Storage, Compute Autoscaling, GPU support, Cluster DNS, Pod and service networking)
4. Provide a cluster name, create a cluster IAM role, choose stable kubernetes version and click on 'Next'. (There are some more options present in the page for customization).
5. Choose the VPC, subnets for high availability, cluster endpoint access (options are: public,public and private,private).
6. Choose observability as per requirement.
7. Choose Add-ons and configure them as per requirements.
8. Review all configurations and click on 'Create'. It will take some time for the cluster to be created and running.
